summary: (3e)-3,7-dimethylocta-1,3,6-triene and 4S-limonene synthase are related through their involvement in the biosynthesis of terpenes. The context discusses various monoterpene synthases, including 4S-limonene synthase, which is responsible for synthesizing limonene, a compound that can be derived from (3e)-3,7-dimethylocta-1,3,6-triene. This indicates a biochemical pathway where (3e)-3,7-dimethylocta-1,3,6-triene may serve as a substrate or intermediate in the enzymatic reactions catalyzed by 4S-limonene synthase, linking them in the context of terpene biosynthesis.
